		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message27331851">Too bad many of these CGd cars still drive on the roads of Japan in 201(4?). As long as CGI doesn't stick out like a sore thumb, I don't mind it. It can even be great when there is no conventional animation at all besides it like in most space (mecha) anime the popular example ARS Nova. <br />
<br />
But as gonzo-qt already said, CGI does still seem to have a problem with animating human bodies or movements. I'm pretty sure technology is advanced enough to make it work without cringeworthiness but studios are either too lazy or don't want to invest the neccessary dolla. Another example of terrible CGI on humans can be found in Kakumeiki Bestvrave's spacesuit battle episode. I tired to figure out for a minute why the humans in spacesuits look weird and different till I realized that CGI is to blame.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
