		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message27378555">Haha. About obvious CGI, there's actually a TVTrope for that: <a href="http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ConspicuousCG" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><a href="http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ConspicuousCG" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ConspicuousCG</a></a><br />
<br />
I'm usually the type of person that doesn't really notice CGI unless someone points it out to me. And even when I see it, I don't really mind. After all, if every show that aired had perfect animation, we wouldn't have as many shows to watch! In general, people do tend to implement new technology as soon as possible, so a little wrong use is simply human nature and something to deal with. <br />
<br />
