		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message27381255">I don't have much to add. I just think that the biggest problem with CGI is how fast it ages. Stuff that may have looked decent or passable a year ago (or less!) often looks super awful now. More stylized works, or anime with higher budgets, sometimes manage to sidestep this falling, but these are rare cases. This sacrifice in longevity is enough to make me lament its prevalence, but I'm aware the use of CGI is often out of necessity (lack of budget/time). 仕方が無い。<br />
